</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/02 5:23:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Target cap</span><hr size=1> &quot;Can you kill 1 XP bearing mob using al'kabor? Then, with that design, you can kill 50 XP bearing mobs using al'kabor.&quot;<br>
<br>
No.  Go ahead and try without running out of mana, go to any spot and fight any monster, do your damnest using kiting rooting, just blasting, have people keep it stuck, do anything you want.  It won't work, you can't get xps with these crapfest spells.  You know why?  The damage is too low and the mana cost it too high plus the recast time is very long; if you were very conversant with these spells you'd know how true this is.  See, if you could use Al'Kabor spells to kill monsters for xps people WOULD ALREADY DO IT because you can kill 5 with it instead of 4 and don't need to bunch them as tightly (the area is bigger).  They don't, for good reason.<br>
<br>
As a simple example:<br>
<br>
Inferno of Al'Kabor (level 53)<br>
Damage 750 (L53) to 800 (L58 )  <br>
Range to Target: 200 feet<br>
Area Effect Range: 35 feet<br>
Mana Required: 625<br>
Casting Time: 5.0 seconds<br>
Spell Recovery: 2.50 seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 9.0 seconds<br>
<br>
Damage per mana, base: 1.2<br>
Damage per mana, max: 1.28<br>
Damage per second, base: 50.0<br>
Damage per second, max: 57.14<br>
<br>
Pillar of Frost (level 51)<br>
Damage 755 (L51) to 800 (L60)<br>
Mana Required: 325<br>
Casting Time: 4.50 seconds<br>
Spell Recovery: 2.50 seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 6.0 seconds<br>
<br>
Damage per mana, base: 2.3<br>
Damage per mana, max: 2.46<br>
Damage per second, base: 71.9<br>
Damage per second, max: 76.19<br>
<br>
Al'Kabor spells use almost twice as much mana, take longer to cast, longer to recast, do less damage, and that's for a spell three levels higher or more.  They really, honestly are that awful.<br>
<br>
Some more numbers: Mana total at level 53 for Wizard at 255 INT: around 3000, plus some gear (lets say 3500).<br>
<br>
AlKabor Damage with this mana: 3750 damage.  Go ahead at level 53 and find a monster that <br>
1) give you any xps<br>
2) stays at range for you to use Al'Kabor on (i.e. you can kill using an AE spell)<br>
3) comes in swarms of over 5<br>
4) has fewer than 4000 hps and doesn't regen fast enough to make a difference between the 9 second blasts<br>
<br>
Incidentally, the post 50 Al'Kabor spells aren't as godawful as the lower level ones either.  They are still crap but not AS crappy.<br>
<br>
Feel free to show how this would be abused again.<br>
<br>
-Grimstaff Theurgist &quot;Wizards like it clustered&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 5/4/02 2:15:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushardanaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shardanaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/4/02 9:29:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Target cap</span><hr size=1> Al'kabor spells will never be useful until you have a situation where you have  alot of mobs spread out over an area that cannot be mezzed.  Given the area radius on these spells, they're also dangerous to use--distance is tougher to judge than with Pillar and Rain. <br>
<br>
Thing is, we'll never see this type of encounter, given the way the game works, and if we do, it'll be like the ring wars--where it's more efficient to burn down one mob than it is to hurt all of them.<br>
<br>
At least Pilar's are good for quadding and, occasionally, for a ghetto xp group if you can get the melees to split.  But then it's only because of the insane mana effieciency that beats out Draught once you get to even two targets.<br>
<br>
Al'Kabor's?  No.<br>
<br>
As for rains, they're not hard to use, really, I've been using them in XP groups / raids since 55 or so.  If even two waves hit (which they usually do, in my experience) its more efficient than draught and at least seems to draw less aggro.  If you're worried about a mob wandering out of the rain and over to you, stand at the edge of the rain.  They'll still get hit.<br>
<br>
Yeah, the resists could use some reducing, and I'd like it to hit more, but the post-50 rains really aren't a problem anymore, imo.<br>
<br>
--Shardanaan Stormherald<br>
Sorcerer, Torvo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/4/02 3:51:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I admit that one wizard can't kill with it.  BUT 2 can.<br>
<br>
Sheesh, I've already explained this.  Ok, here goes again:<br>
<br>
2 wizards could.  Hand-off kiting (kite to near oom, zone/abscond/camp, other wizard kites to oom/mob death, first wizard finishes).<br>
<br>
That brings the HP threshold up to 7500 HPs+.  Oh look, same threshold as pillar spells.  But, instead of 4 mobs at a time, you have (SPAWN_POINTS/2) mobs at a time.<br>
<br>
2 wizards could quad every wyvern in CS.  Every single last one of them.  At once.  This scales poorly.<br>
<br>
That is why infinite target spells are nearly unbalanceable.<br>
<br>
Yes, al'kabor spells are CRAP.  Junk junk junk.  But, my claim is not that they are good now, but that your solution doesn't work.<br>
<br>
I mean, how about stuff like:<br>
<br>
Add a 0 time mez to al'kabor spells.  This will prevent them from ever breaking mez (won't land on a mez'd target).<br>
<br>
Double damage on stationary targets (including rooted ones).<br>
<br>
Keep the 5 target limit.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/02 6:55:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> If you TRULY think anyone COULD get every wyvern at once, let alone would get the opportunity to actually be there without anyone else hunting them, you'd have a point - but you know as well as I do that ain't gonna happen.  It's hard enough to get four spawns let alone take even one more.  Then lets factor something else in: how many times do you want to cast atol's spirit shackles?  Each one of those takes away from maximum cast of Al'Kabors because they take MANA. <br>
<br>
Hypothetical stuff like this is pointless.  What if bards could gather every raptor at once and kill them one at a time using charm and selos?  Oops, I guess technically it's possible, on paper at least!  I sure as hell wouldn't try it, but bards are nuts anyway.  NERF SELO'S!!!  Or wait, maybe the risk and trouble is way over the reward, maybe its such a limited, wierd area that it doesn't hurt the game, and maybe, just maybe coming up with bizarre scenarios like that has no bearing on the actual game! <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 5/5/02 7:52:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushardanaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shardanaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/02 3:29:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Besides, the whole 2-person quad is extremely, extremely difficult to do anyway.  If you haven't tried it, here's how it works--<br>
<br>
Only three mobs will run after one person at any one time, if more than one person is on the hate list. (obviously, this wouldn't apply if you had eight mobs and two people, but I haven;'t tried that)<br>
<br>
Tried this with Giants in FM, wyverns, etc, mostly a long time ago, but unless they've changed the aggro rules, it still applies.  I've rounded up a quad, snared, burned twice, then had the other caster burn....and one ALWAYS goes after them.  Every damned time.<br>
<br>
So even in this limited, well-nigh impossible situation, it's STILL mostly useless.<br>
<br>
It's fire support for helping a group of forties in MM. <br>
<br>
Oh, wait, there's Jyll's.  And Winds of Gelid.<br>
<br>
--Shardanaan Stormherald<br>
Sorcerer, Torv <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/02 11:33:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> double quad</span><hr size=1> Shard -- yep, I've seen that issue.  Hence the forced handoff (only one wizard holds aggro at one time).  The concerns with bonds wearing off are serious, probably drop the HP cap on killable mobs by a bit.<br>
<br>
And yes, Grim, it is hard.  But, the limiting factor on a wizards XP with a infinite-target ranged spell is the number of spawn points of non casters in a zone.<br>
<br>
The spell you proposed would be useful in killing trains of greens, yes.  But my point is it would also be useful for mega-kiting.  And why do you want a spell good for killing trains of greens?  You already have PBAOEs.  I don't think Verant implementing that spell would be worth the risk.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hypothetical stuff like this is pointless.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, Hypothetical stuff like that is the point of thinking about spell ideas.  I mean, I'll admit that your spell will not cause any imbalance in how people currently play the game.  If you cast your spell instead of a spell you would right now, but didn't change your gameplay in ANY other way, there would be no problem.<br>
<br>
But players ADAPT.  They look at spells, min max, and try to set up ways to maximize their own advantage.  If you outlaw the hypothetical, your spells will not handle adapting players at all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What if bards could gather every raptor at once and kill them one at a time using charm and selos? Oops, I guess technically it's possible, on paper at least!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, bard charm (at that level) eats mana.  Bards regain mana at 1 mana per tick, no matter what (maybe 2 sitting).  The bard would run out of mana by the time they killed too many raptors, I'd think.  The rate of killing raptors is limited by the bards mana regen, and the requirement that a PC-controlled entity does half the damage to sub-56 mobs in order for XP/loot to occur.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I sure as hell wouldn't try it, but bards are nuts anyway. NERF SELO'S!!! Or wait, maybe the risk and trouble is way over the reward, maybe its such a limited, wierd area that it doesn't hurt the game, and maybe, just maybe coming up with bizarre scenarios like that has no bearing on the actual game! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Or maybe it doesn't work?<br>
<br>
If you are going to change spells, beyond just tweaking numbers, you HAVE to think up bizarre scenarios.  Why?  Because imbalance often happens in the land of the bizaare.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I disaggree with you about your idea.  =)<br>
<br>
Any opinions on mine?  Tear it apart!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/02 12:08:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: double quad</span><hr size=1> It works, and bards do it.  Its just risky as hell, and the reason you can't toss hypothetical problems out that are absurd in their extreme is a pretty standard problem presently.  People know just enough logic to realize that ANYTHING can be argued, there is no way of humanly proving anything to ZERO doubt.  Thus, you can find a loophole in anything, no matter what, and pretend this is a major problem.  I can 100% guarantee nobody would EVER EVER end up kiting more than 5 monsters at once no matter how careful lucky and incredibly rare this ended up being.  It's way too much risk, way too much trouble, and I again suggest you look at how much mana it would cost to snare every one of those monsters you seem to believe people will have not only opportunity but desire to kite en masse. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/02 1:10:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I just realized something:  With decent coordination, you don't have to gate to clear aggro -- al'kabors have a large enough radius to let 2 people who work HARD at it both nuke.<br>
<br>
It would, admittedly, take coordination.  But I doubt it would be beyond a pair of good players.<br>
<br>
So, they both go and aggro some mobs.  And they both start snareing.  Does the L 51 snare have a target limit?  Anyone know for sure?<br>
<br>
Lets assume a limit of 4.  And, half of all snares are wasted.<br>
<br>
So, thats 75 mana per mob, pretty generous with wasted snares.<br>
<br>
Conservative: 75 * Mob_Count + Max_mob_Hps<br>
to<br>
Generous: 25 * Mob_Count + Max_mob_Hps * .8<br>
<br>
Wyverns have about 3200 HPs, and are blue at 52, most light blue at 54 (half xp).<br>
<br>
Two wizards could do... 37 of the suckers at L 53, with 3 k mana each, or so.  Half of the mana used is on snares, conservatively.  Generously, 133 of them.  Both of these numbers are limited by the number of spawn points.<br>
<br>
Ok, lets get really busy.  3 wizards, 5000 hp mobs.  53 of them.  4 wizards, 93 mobs.  Using conservative numbers.<br>
<br>
Using generous numbers, 3 can do 193, 2 can do 73.<br>
<br>
These numbers look ridiculous.  And they are.  I don't expect 3 wizards to kill 193 mobs at once.  I don't expect 4 wizards to be able to kite in syncro.  But, people WILL try this sort of thing.  And Verant would have to test the hell of of it before releasing it.  They would have to get good kiters, train them in new tactics, and see if it was possible to kill 100 mobs from range in some of the new huge outdoor zones.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think there would be wizards good enough to pull it off.  Hell, you could even try it for a lark -- penta kite 5 mobs with a wizard friend.  XP will be worse than quadding, but it might help in balancing your idea.<br>
<br>
Your change does have the advantage of turning quad kiting into a small group activity (large groups require WAY to much coordination).  A group of JUST wizards.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/02 9:02:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> The problem isn't &quot;can this theoretically be done&quot; its more &quot;is there anywhere it COULD be done&quot;<br>
<br>
Its not easy even getting 4 targets in Cobolt scar, the whole &quot;get all the wyverns at once&quot; thing is absurd.  I challenge you to come up with a zone with not only kitable area and xp granting monsters, but enough spawns to actually do more than 5 at once.  And remember, Atols only lasts a given duration (the max is 4, I guarantee you), and it will wear off as you go along... you have to keep ALL of them snared at once, resnaring time means others will start to break.  You really are in a bad way if you try to do more than even 5, assuming you could get that many.  Also remember that Al'Kabor casts 50% slower than pillar spells overall. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 5/12/02 11:11:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/02 10:53:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.totalnetsolutions.net/nightwatch/images/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Grim's hitting a point that everyone else seems to be missing in all of this - Al'Kabor's spells cast 2x as long as pillars do.  Even snared mobs will catch up to you before you finish casting, making kiting near, if not completely, impossible.<br>
<br>
Add to taht the difficulty of getting enough mobs to make this possible.<br>
<br>
Add to this the difficulty of passing off between the 2 wizards successfully<br>
<br>
Add to this the fact that both wizards would ahve to be in-zone when the kill-shot is made (which requires decent timing of zoning and kiting), or the effort is wasted for one of them<br>
<br>
Add to this the difficulty of keeping all mobs grouped together when wizard A zones, without having to re-group them.<br>
<br>
Add to this the difficulty of keeping them all snared so that kiting is possible.<br>
<br>
Then add up the amount of time it would take for the kills to be made, and see if all that difficulty is worth it, when you could just be quadding instead.<br>
